<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Mon 23 Oct 2006
From: T Jacob John <vlr_tjjohn@sancharnet.in>
Source: The Hindu (Chennai Edition) Mon 23 Oct 2006)
<http://www.hindu.com/2006/10/23/stories/2006102311440100.htm>

Hand-foot-and-mouth disease (HFMD) in children in Kerala
-----------------------------------------------
In the absence of systematic and comprehensive disease surveillance
in the various states of India, we learn about outbreaks only from
newspapers. Obviously only newsworthy outbreaks are reported.
According to this newspaper report, some 200 children with HFMD have
been seen in one hospital in Kozhikode (previously Calicut) by one
pediatrician during the past several months. No virological study was
reported, even though the hospital concerned is a part of the local
Calicut Medical Colllege.
Since there was no mention of death, I would surmise that there was
none. Therefore, it is unlikely that the cause is Human enterovirus
71, which may cause large outbreaks of HFMD, neurological diseases
and some mortality. Causes of benign HFMD are Coxsackievirus A16 or
any of the other enteroviruses that may cause HFMD, namely, Human
coxsackieviruses A4, A5, A9, A10, B2 & B5.
--
